1979;;A Nightingale Sang in Berkeley Square;;American;;Ralph Thomas;;David Niven, Elke Sommer, Richard Jordan;;crime comedy;;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/A_Nightingale_Sang_in_Berkeley_Square_(film);;Pinky (Jordan) is released from prison and has decided to go straight from now on, but takes a job as a maintenance man at a large bank, which gives him a lot of undue attention from "Ivan the Terrible" (Niven), the local hoodlum. By using Pinky, Ivan hopes to rob the bank and Pinky starts to liken to the idea of going back to his old ways.